In short, while 2020's bitcoin halving is met with a substantial decline in price from $10k, miners are not in as big of a trouble as they seem.\n\nMining execs expect the industry to expand over the medium-term, especially if bitcoin price starts to climb.

There will be short-term drop in bitcoin hash rate after the halving.\n\nBut, Poolin VP Alejandro De La Torre @bitentrepreneur said  that after the halving, miners are more clearly able to predict their revenues over the next 4 years, and it will lead to mining expansion. https://t.co/Lby53QuFo9
